      "raw_text": "u At the Spokane high school audi\ntorium this evening the debating\nteam from Davenport will meet the\nSpokane debaters in contest for in\nterscholastic forensic honors.\n\n\nWarren w. Tolman. president of\nthe school board, will preside over the\nmeeting. The subject for debate is,\n''Resolved, That American munich\npalities of 100000 or over should own\nand operate their street railways\"\n\n\nSpokane will have charge of the\nnegative side and will be represented\nby Miss May Worthington. Cecil Mar\ntin and Wilbur Hoskyn.\n\n\nThe judges are Harry M. Shafer of\nthe Cheney Normal school, J. e. Blu\nchanan of the State Normal at Che\nney and Professor w. G. Beach OF\nWashington Agricultural college\nProfessor Mattoon of Garfield will\nact as alternate Judge.\n\n\nCity Superintendent J. A. Tormey\nwill give the baccalaureate sermon\nto members of the 1905 graduating\nclass at Westminster Congregational\nchurch Sunday morning."
    }
